.DT
query_number_left
Disk World creator help
query_number_left

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
query_number_left -  This function returns the quantity of particular object available to be cloned on demand.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int query_number_left(string name)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^name%^RESET%^ - is the short name of the object you wish to query.
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the number left, returns INFINITE_LEFT if the shop has an infinite
number, returns -1 if the item isn't stocked.
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/shops/inherit/clone_on_demand.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function returns the quantity of particular object available
to be cloned on demand. In matching which object is the one in
question it uses the short name of the object, which is passed as
an argument to the function.
.EP

